HB 406 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Mike Johnson
Abstract: Requires the state Dept. of Education to conduct a study and report to the
legislature relative to interscholastic high school athletics.
Proposed law requires the state Dept. of Education to conduct a study on the direction and
regulation of interscholastic high school athletics through a cooperative endeavor agreement
with a nonprofit corporation and submit a written report of findings and conclusions to the
House and Senate education committees, the House Committee on Appropriations, and the
Senate Committee on Finance by March 1, 2027, that includes, at a minimum, the following:
(1) Potential nonprofit corporations with which to execute such a cooperative endeavor
agreement.
(2) A plan of action and potential timeline for how such a cooperative endeavor
agreement would be implemented beginning with the 2028-2029 school year.
(3) Funding and cost considerations.
(4) Transitional considerations.
(5) Recommendations relative to legislation necessary to fully implement the direction
and regulation of interscholastic athletics through such a cooperative endeavor
agreement.
(Adds R.S. 17:176.3)
